    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban the use of Prong Collars",
        "additional_details": "They work by causing discomfort/pain and can cause injury. They can cause physical and psychological damage and can worsen reactivity in dogs.\r\n \r\nTo prevent suffering. Causing pain to a dog is not only unethical but can make it more likely that a dog will react aggressively as it may associate certain things with pain.",
        "background": "Prohibit the use of prong collars on dogs. These are aversive \u2018tools\u2019 that individuals and some dog trainers use to prevent a dog pulling or lunging.",
